	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">cpow wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I believe the appearance of amputation is not what you're after...</div><br />You'd be correct. Though characters in <a href="https://pineight.com/mw/index.php?title=Category:Pictures_of_polis" class="postlink">some of my works</a> resemble high leg amputees, this is not one of them. And I don't really feel like writing about hand amputees because fine manipulators (especially the opposable thumb) are a big part of what distinguishes human-type characters from more &quot;animal&quot; characters. One might justify a mitten hand as an oven mitt, but then the flipped version (the character's other hand that doesn't have a mitt on it) would need a hand.<br /><br />tl;dr: Mind the thumb.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


